KEY:
'-' = Not Completed
'X' = Completed

Create Objects:
X Floor (Textured with checkerboard pattern)
X 4 Walls, 1 Ceiling (All Colored/Textured)
- Table (Top textured with wood pattern)
- Desk Lamp
X Copper Ball
X Polished Silver Ball
- Pair of Dice (with texture-mapped dots)
- Textured picture on the wall (when lights are off)

Create Light Sources:
X 3 Overhead Lights (1 Red, 1 Green, 1 Blue) on the ceiling (Draw a colored ball to represent the light source position/color)
X Desk Lamp Light (Dim white light, about 75% intensity)
- Bright (white) spotlight/flashlight from the camera's view (30 degrees)

Navigation (Functionality):
X Look up/down (90 degrees)
X Turn left/right (360 degrees)
X Move forward/backward
X Move side to side
X (SET KEYSTROKE): Button to set the camera back at a starting position
X (SET KEYSTROKE): Button to level the camera's gaze (look DIRECTLY AHEAD, not up or down)
- Camera CANNOT walk through walls, set x and z boundaries

Other functionality:
X 'h': prints a help message in the console (Text from help.txt)
X 0-4: Turns off one of each of the lights (There are 5 lights total, see light sources above)
    - When all lights (except camera flashlight) are off, the textured picture on the wall appears ***
- (SET KEYSTROKE): The Copper Ball rolls around (in a circle) on the table top. Pressing same button stops the movement (Animation)
- (SET KEYSTROKE): The Polished Silver Ball rolls around (in a circle) on the table top. Pressing same button stops the movement (Animation)
- (SET KEYSTROKE): The dice animate (roll or spin) for a few seconds and then stop

